  "title": "Senior Compliance Officer L2 - Private Bank, Contract",
  "description": "<p>Duration: 6 - 12 Months Contract <br /><br /><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Perform Level 2 (L2) reviews, independently assessing, concluding, and documenting risk decisions for high and complex client cases</li><li>Take full ownership of periodic KYC / CDD reviews, ensuring client files meet regulatory and internal requirements</li><li>Independently review and assess high-risk client cases, including: PEPs and related parties, clients with complex or layered ownership structures, cross-border and multi-jurisdictional relationships</li><li>Make risk assessments and conclusions based on client profile, activity, screening results, and adverse media</li><li>Identify unusual or higher-risk issues and decide on appropriate actions, including escalation where required</li><li>Review client transaction activity, name screening alerts, and adverse media to identify potential concerns</li><li>Handle ad-hoc KYC/CDD requests from auditors, regulators, and Head Office in a timely and well-documented manner</li><li>Support regulatory examinations, internal audits, and compliance reviews</li><li>Contribute to process improvements and compliance initiatives</li><li>Stay updated on AML/CFT regulatory and internal policy changes</li><li>Provide guidance and support to junior team members to ensure consistent review standards</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum 7 years of AML/KYC experience, with hands-on exposure to periodic reviews and high-risk client cases</li><li>Strong working knowledge of MAS Notice 626 and applicable AML/CFT regulations and guidelines, with proven ability to apply regulatory requirements in a Private Banking environment.</li><li>Experience dealing with PEPs, complex ownership structures, and cross-border clients</li><li>Experience supporting audits or regulatory reviews is an advantage</li></ul><p>Email: <a href=\"mailto:nurul.amirah@gmprecruit.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">nurul.amirah@gmprecruit.com</a></p><p><strong>** This Singapore-based position is opened to Singaporeans only.</strong></p><p>We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified. </p><p>GMP Technologies (S) Pte Ltd   |   EA Licence:11C3793   |   Nurul Amirah |   Registration No: R22108940</p><p><em></em><a href=\"https://www.gmprecruit.com/legal/privacy-policy/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><em></em></a><a href=\"https://us-west-2.protection.sophos.com?d=e2i.com.sg&u=aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZTJpLmNvbS5zZy9wZHBhLw==&i=NThlNDdhOGMyYmI5N2YwZmQxZDk4NjQw&t=cWdqRFV0Uy80RjN3MDlSYmM1dS85VTRxVTRoYVlXdWFyWTYzaGlVS3k0TT0=&h=1ad0460f503340658fbeab159c31256f&s=AVNPUEhUT0NFTkNSWVBUSVaVGQEVMuPAipiPENS4aadnRg3RqoiWpHBKgNtumWhHjA\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><em></em></a></p>",
